  "doc_id": "53081",
  "text": "Impulse responses from each loudspeaker to grid points in a planar measurement region were measured. These impulse responses were used to obtain sound pressure distributions of the original and reproduced sound fields by post-processing. The impulse responses were measured by using time-stretched pulse (TSP) signals [CITATION_1] in 2.2×1.6-m regions (shaded region in Fig. 4) at intervals of 1.5 cm, i.e., 144×108 points. The signals of the linear microphone array were obtained in the same room. The microphone array was set at the same position as the loudspeaker array, and the impulse responses from the loudspeakers at S1 and S2 were measured.",
